        "rich_text_CLCaTX": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Tips for Formal Jewelry Styling",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Tips for Formal Jewelry Styling</h3><ol><li>Match Metals with Dress Colors: Silver or platinum complements cool tones, while gold pairs beautifully with warm hues. Rose gold can add a modern, romantic touch.<br/><br/></li><li>Balance Statement Pieces: If wearing a statement necklace, opt for simpler earrings and bracelets to avoid overpowering the outfit.<br/><br/></li><li>Consider Neckline and Sleeve Length: Necklaces should complement the neckline, and bracelets or cuffs work best when sleeves are shorter or fitted.<br/><br/></li><li>Pay Attention to Hair and Makeup: Hair updos or sleek styles allow earrings and necklaces to shine. Similarly, subtle makeup balances bold jewelry pieces.<br/><br/></li><li>Occasion Awareness: The jewelry chosen should suit the formality of the event—black-tie galas allow for more dramatic pieces, while business formal events require understated elegance.<br/><br/></li></ol><p>By carefully choosing your formal wear jewelry and considering factors like outfit color, neckline, and event type, you can create a cohesive and sophisticated look that leaves a lasting impression.</p>",
            "custom_id": "styling",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_rQKzCe": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How to Coordinate Jewelry and Clothes",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>How to Coordinate Jewelry and Clothes</h2><p>Coordinating jewelry and clothes is an art that involves balancing colors, styles, and textures. Here are some strategies:</p><ul><li>Color Matching: Pair gold jewelry with warm tones like reds, oranges, and browns. Silver or platinum works well with cool tones such as blues, greens, and purples.<br/><br/></li><li>Occasion Consideration: Match your jewelry to the formality of the event. Casual outfits benefit from minimalist pieces, while formal events allow for more elaborate designs.<br/><br/></li><li>Balance: Avoid over-accessorizing. If you wear a statement necklace, keep earrings and bracelets subtle. Let one piece be the focal point of your ensemble.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": "coordinate",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ADDTPa": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Color Coordination: Jewelry and Outfits",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Color Coordination: Jewelry and Outfits</h2><p>Understanding color coordination can transform your jewelry game. Here’s a quick guide:</p><ul><li>Warm Tones: Gold, copper, and rose gold jewelry complement outfits with reds, yellows, or oranges.<br/><br/></li><li>Cool Tones: Silver, white gold, or platinum enhances blue, green, or purple clothing.<br/><br/></li><li>Neutral Outfits: Neutral shades like black, white, or beige allow you to experiment with colorful gemstones, mixed metals, or layered designs.<br/></li></ul><p>Matching jewelry to dress type while keeping color harmony in mind ensures a stylish and cohesive look.</p>",
            "custom_id": "color",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_7bxGmb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Tips for Mixing and Matching",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Tips for Mixing and Matching</h2><p>Mixing and matching jewelry allows you to express personal style while keeping your outfit cohesive:</p><ul><li>Layering: Combine delicate chains or bracelets for a chic, modern look.<br/><br/></li><li>Contrasting Styles: Pair modern jewelry with traditional outfits for a fusion effect.<br/><br/></li><li>Personal Style: Ultimately, jewelry should reflect your individuality. Experiment with different styles, textures, and colors to discover what works best for you.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": "mixmatch",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_7gJGUd": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Lucira Jewelry: Elevating Your Style",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Lucira Jewelry: Elevating Your Style</h2><p><a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a> offers a curated collection of ethically sourced, <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/lab-grown-diamond-jewellery\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lab Grown DIamond Jewellery\">Lab Grown Diamond Jewellery</a> that combines elegance and modern design. Their range includes solitaire engagement rings, statement necklaces, and versatile everyday pieces suitable for different outfits. By choosing Lucira Jewelry, you can enjoy timeless pieces that are sustainable, stylish, and perfectly coordinated with your wardrobe.</p>",
            "custom_id": "lucira",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_CNg3En": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion: Your Jewelry, Your Statement",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Conclusion: Your Jewelry, Your Statement</h2><p>Matching jewelry with outfits is all about balance, style, and confidence. Whether it’s casual wear, formal events, or traditional attire, selecting the right jewelry enhances your look and expresses your personality. By following these tips on how to coordinate jewelry and clothes, understanding color coordination, and experimenting with different styles, you can create outfits that leave a lasting impression.</p><p>Explore Lucira Jewelry’s collection today and discover the perfect pieces to complement your wardrobe. Elevate your style while embracing sustainable, Lab Grown Diamonds.</p>",
            "custom_id": "conclusion",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        }
