    "faqs_jWyqCp": {
      "type": "faq-section",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_Xa7a9G": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "1. How do I match jewelry with outfits effectively?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>To match jewelry with outfits, consider the type of clothing, the occasion, and the colors involved. For casual wear, opt for subtle and minimal pieces. For formal or traditional outfits, choose statement jewelry that complements the style and color of your attire. Balancing the jewelry without over-accessorizing is key.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_rcaANV": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "2. What is the best jewelry for different outfits?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>The best jewelry depends on the outfit:</p><ul><li>Casual outfits: Delicate studs, thin bracelets, and simple chains.<br/></li><li>Formal wear: Statement necklaces, chandelier earrings, cuffs, and cocktail rings.<br/></li><li>Traditional attire: Jhumkas, bangles, maang tikkas, and collar necklaces.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_HMGtjz": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "3. How do I match jewelry to dress type?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Matching jewelry to dress type involves considering the neckline, sleeve length, and fabric. For example, a V-neck gown pairs well with a layered necklace, while a strapless dress works beautifully with a statement choker. Long sleeves or intricate patterns may require minimal jewelry to avoid overwhelming the look.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_UHKzLJ": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "4. How can I coordinate jewelry and clothes by color?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Color coordination is essential for a cohesive look:</p><ul><li>Warm tones: Pair gold or rose gold jewelry with reds, oranges, and yellows.<br/><br/></li><li>Cool tones: Silver, platinum, or white gold complements blues, greens, and purples.<br/><br/></li><li>Neutral outfits: Use colorful gemstones or mixed-metal jewelry to add visual interest.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_eAdDeB": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "5. Can I mix and match jewelry styles?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Yes! Mixing and matching jewelry can create unique and stylish looks. Pair modern pieces with traditional outfits or layer delicate bracelets and necklaces for a contemporary effect. Ensure balance by keeping one piece as the focal point to avoid clutter.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_jktigb": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "6. What jewelry is best for formal events?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>For formal events, statement pieces like chandelier earrings, layered necklaces, cocktail rings, and elegant cuffs work best. Match the jewelry style with the outfit’s elegance and the event’s formality for a sophisticated appearance.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
